sec.p:
The time derivatives will use the following notation: X’ = dX/dt. In a generalised experimental set-up, the quantum of source exergy ∆E is delivered into the experimental space and converted into thermodynamic work ∆W. This work packet ∆W might push the system into an elevated metastable state ∆G. In a special case of infinitely slow delivery, a reversible change of ∆G = ∆W = ∆E is possible (Jarzynski 1997; Toyabe et al. 2010; An et al. 2014). A microscopic exergy efficiency e for a realistic, finite time process should be introduced: ∆G = e∆E. The primary exergy efficiency e shall be within the interval of zero to unity. Zero represents zero or negative changes in the free energy, and unity represents positive and thermodynamically reversible energy storage. The chemical information potential, B, is introduced here. The positive stored energy ∆G results in a corresponding stored information potential ∆Bgen(erated) (Eq. 1) in bits of information:1ΔBgen=eΔE/kBTln2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
