As is the case with all inventions derived when an opportunity presents itself, the moment sufficient stored information potential B is accumulated, an opportunity to consume the stored information becomes apparent. Because B is also accumulated exergy, Eaccumulated = B kBT ln(2), it is possible to invent a heterotrophic process (Stoker et al. 1990) that benefits from ‘metabolising’ stored B. Subsequently, the basic equation for the experimental set-up and information generation B’gen Eq. 2 becomes Eq. 4, and Eq. 3 for B′ becomes Eq. 5:4B’gen=εE’/kBTln2+εFB’consuming\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
